<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 SOUTH BAY TEAMS WILL SQUARE OFF IN 4-A PLAYOFFS AND 2 OTHERS ADVANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four South Bay high schools will play semifinal-round games Saturday night at 
7:30 in the CIF Southern Section girls basketball playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
In a match-up of two area teams, fourth-seeded West Torrance (20-5) battles 
Bishop Montgomery (17-9) in a 4-A Division game at South Torrance High. 
</P>
<P>
Both teams boast excellent point guards. Bishop Montgomery is led by Lily 
Cabaleiro, who scored 25 points Wednesday night in the Knights' 51-44 upset 
over top-seeded La Habra. West's premier player is Rosa Olloque, who had 18 
points in the Warriors' 48-35 quarterfinal victory over Los Altos. 
</P>
<P>
The winner advances to the 4-A championship game at 6:45 p.m. Friday at Cal 
Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
In the 5-AA Division, top-seeded Morningside (26-3) faces Chino (25-2) at 
Ontario. The Lady Monarchs came back from an 18-point second-quarter deficit 
Wednesday night to defeat host Channel Islands of Oxnard, 66-55, behind the 
play of center Lisa Leslie (26 points, 21 rebounds, seven blocked shots) and 
forward Janet Davis (10 points, 16 rebounds). 
</P>
<P>
The 5-AA championship will be decided Friday night at 8:30 at UC Irvine. 
Morningside is going after its third straight Southern Section crown. 
</P>
<P>
In the 3-AA Division, second-seeded Palos Verdes (26-4) travels to meet 
Estancia of Costa Mesa (14-12) at University High in Irvine. The winner plays 
for the title at 8:30 Wednesday night at Cal Poly Pomona. ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
