<P>
Vatican to Celebrate Sistine Restoration: The Vatican plans an exhibition, an 
international symposium and books to mark the completion of the restoration of 
Michelangelo's Sistine Chapel ceiling frescoes. The Vatican said Thursday that 
an exhibition will open March 25, marking the end of a 10-year project that 
cleaned and restored the Renaissance artist's 16th-Century masterpieces. The 
cleaning of the Sistine has been one of the most ambitious and significant art 
restoration projects in history. CLAUDIA PUIG 
