<P>
Grammy Ratings Improve: Ratings for the Grammy Awards telecast on Wednesday 
night were up significantly over last year's and nearly equaled those of the 
recent American Music Awards. The 3 1/2-hour CBS broadcast averaged an 18.9 
rating, compared to a 16 last year -- meaning it was seen in about 17.4 million 
homes, or 3 million more than the 1989 show. For the hours between 8 and 11 
p.m., Wednesday's ceremonies averaged a 19.7 rating, just shy of the 20 figure 
that ABC wracked up during the same three hours for the American Music Awards 
on Jan. 22. CLAUDIA PUIG 
