<TEXT>
<P>
Musical Chairs: Columbia/Tri Star incurred royal wrath after a seating mix up 
at the Buckingham Palace premiere of "Steel Magnolias." 
</P>
<P>
One person's wrong choice of the seat reserved for Olympia Dukakis next to 
Prince Charles led to seating pandemonium. When Dukakis and actress Julia 
Roberts showed and had nowhere to sit, the Prince tried to move and nobody knew 
where to go. The Palace sent a letter of complaint about the musical chairs 
game to Columbia/Tri Star's London office, expressing unhappiness that the 
Prince and Princess of Wales had to move seats. The next royal premiere is "The 
Hunt for Red October" on April 17. CLAUDIA PUIG 
