<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MASSACHUSETTS; 
</P>
<P>
LIMITS ON CLINIC PROTESTERS REINSTATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Massachusetts' highest court reinstated an order barring demonstrators from 
blocking abortion clinics, but the group Operation Rescue said it will obey a 
"higher law" and continue to protest. The Supreme Judicial Court ruled 4 to 1 
that the injunction places only minimal limitations on protesters and does not 
threaten their First Amendment rights. A spokeswoman for Operation Rescue, 
which has staged several protests at clinics, said her anti-abortion group will 
continue its activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
