<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CHULA VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Detectives are investigating the shooting death of Cadelario Aguirre. 
</P>
<P>
Aguirre was last seen alive about 9:30 p.m. Wednesday, when his housemate and 
her daughter left the home in the 100 block of Via de Laurencio to drive their 
housekeeper home, said Deputy Robbie Arff. 
</P>
<P>
When they returned about 11 p.m., they found Aguirre lying on the living room 
floor with a gunshot wound to his head. 
</P>
<P>
Arff said that there was no sign of forced entry or struggle. The front door 
was ajar and the back door was open, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Aguirre had reported a burglary in the home about a month ago, Arff said. She 
said that "a significant amount of money" had been stolen at the time. The 
exact amount of money reported stolen was not available. 
