SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CARLSBAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The school board will decide at Wednesday's meeting the future of the former 
Carlsbad High School teacher's aide previously accused of selling steroids to 
three students. 
</P>
<P>
The eight charges against Gregory Tirona of selling a controlled substance were 
dismissed Tuesday after a jury hung 11-1 in favor of acquittal. 
</P>
<P>
Tirona has said he wants to return to the school, where he taught a class for 
suspended students. 
</P>
<P>
School board member Ed Switzer said the board may choose either to retain 
Tirona or refer him to the school's personnel commission for a termination 
hearing. 
</P>
<P>
"As a board member I think I have a strong obligation to protect kids, but by 
the same token, I don't want to falsely accuse an employee," Switzer said. 
