<P>
Caesars World Inc.: The Los Angeles-based hotel and casino company said 
second-quarter profit fell 86% to $1.4 million, primarily because of 
substantially lower win percentages at its casino operations in Nevada. Revenue 
totaled $202.9 million, down 5% from the same period a year ago. The company 
said higher casino payroll and operating costs and higher provisions for bad 
debts also affected the Nevada results. 
</P>
