<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' PAIRINGS; 
</P>
<P>
OCEAN VIEW, LA QUINTA HIT THE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DONNA CARTER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eight Orange County girls' teams remain in the Southern Section basketball 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
All of the semifinal games will be played Saturday night at neutral sites, so 
there are no home-court advantages. 
</P>
<P>
However, winners of Thursday's coin flips were designated as the "home team." 
Being designated the home team gives schools the advantage of playing at a 
gymnasium near their school. 
</P>
<P>
Only two county teams -- Ocean View and La Quinta -- lost coin tosses. 
</P>
<P>
Here are the pairings for each division involving county teams. All of the 
games, except in the 2-AA division, begin at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
5-A Division -- Fourth-seeded Ocean View (26-2) makes its first appearance in 
the semifinals. The Seahawks, who have set a school record for victories in a 
season, travel to Ventura High for their game against top-seeded Buena (25-0). 
</P>
<P>
4-AA Division -- Unseeded Loara (16-10) is the designated home team against 
unseeded Ventura (18-9) at Savanna High. 
</P>
<P>
4-A Division -- Third-seeded La Quinta (25-3), led by Amy Jalewalia, last 
season's state scoring leader, takes on second-seeded Palm Desert (25-2) at 
College of the Desert near Palm Springs. The Aztecs make their first appearance 
in the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
3-AA Division -- Unseeded Estancia (14-12) is the home team against 
second-seeded Palos Verdes (26-4) at University High. 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda, which beat Foothill Thursday night, plays fourth-seeded Alemany 
(20-6). The home team will be determined by a coin flip today. 
</P>
<P>
3-A Division -- Making its first appearance in the semifinals, top-seeded 
Rancho Alamitos (20-3) plays host to San Dimas (16-6) at Bolsa Grande High. 
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Costa Mesa (15-11), led by standout freshman Olivia DiCamilli, plays 
host to second-seeded South Hills (19-5) at Estancia High. 
</P>
<P>
2-AA Division -- Fourth-seeded Santa Margarita (20-6) is the home team against 
unseeded Beaumont (18-6). The game will start at 7 p.m. at Saddleback College. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
