<TEXT>
<P>
An 18-month-old girl drowned in a man-made pond Thursday after wandering 
outside an apartment in Fullerton, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Krystal Lynn Marquis apparently was playing unattended downstairs in the 
apartment of her mother's fiance, Brian Nauenberg, in The Streams complex in 
the 1200 block of Deerpark Drive about 2 p.m., Sgt. Neal Baldwin said. 
</P>
<P>
Nauenberg, who was downstairs, thought Krystal was upstairs with her mother, 
Keary Lynn Sharp, 19, from Garden Grove, police said. When Nauenberg noticed 
the apartment was quiet, he realized the girl had wandered out the patio door. 
Police said Nauenberg ran outside and saw Krystal unconscious in about a foot 
of water in a pond that meanders through the apartment complex. Paramedics were 
called, but the child was pronounced dead at Placentia-Linda Community 
Hospital. 
