<P>
BUSH AIDE TAKES JAB AT LAWYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush's press secretary gave a lighthearted tongue-lashing today to 
the nation's lawyers, saying they "deserve all the criticism they can get." 
</P>
<P>
Marlin Fitzwater made his comment at his regular daily briefing when a reporter 
asked if Bush was criticizing lawyers when he said in a Baltimore speech 
Thursday that the government would help "restore common sense and fairness to 
America's medical malpractice system." 
</P>
<P>
Fitzwater, who is not a lawyer, said, "Lawyers certainly deserve all the 
criticism they can get." 
</P>
<P>
Asked if Bush, also a non-lawyer, shared his feelings, Fitzwater laughingly 
said: "Those are universally held feelings by everyone who's ever dealt with 
the legal establishment. . . . I'm sure all my good friends who are lawyers 
understand." 
</P>
<P>
Fitzwater, who is divorced and recently closed on a new house, did not explain 
the basis of his feelings. 
</P>
