<P>
P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
BIG THREE CAR SALES OFF 15.8% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sales of cars and light trucks assembled in North America by the nation's Big 
Three auto makers dropped 15.8% in mid-February from last year, the companies 
reported today. 
</P>
<P>
General Motors, Ford and Chrysler each had incentive packages in effect during 
the Feb. 11-20 period this year, but the rebates on Chrysler's popular minivans 
that lifted January sales were missing this month. 
</P>
<P>
The Big Three said they sold vehicles at an average daily rate of 29,116 during 
the period this year, compared with a daily average of 34,579 during the same 
time last year. 
</P>
<P>
Car sales fell 17.1% and truck sales, which include minivans, dropped 13.6%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
