<P>
MAN ADMITS SEEKING ELLIS BRIBE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Seattle man pleaded guilty of attempting to extort money from the lawyer of 
Seattle SuperSonics guard Dale Ellis. 
</P>
<P>
"I attempted to get money from an attorney in exchange for giving favorable 
trial testimony on behalf of his client," wrote Guy Thomas, 24, in his plea 
agreement Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas, a nightclub bouncer here, entered the plea to the crime of "bribe 
receiving by a witness" before King County Superior Court Judge J. Kathleen 
Learned. 
</P>
<P>
The crime stems from Ellis' pending case on drunken and reckless-driving 
charges. A hearing has been set for March 20 in Seattle District Court. He has 
pleaded innocent to the charges. 
</P>
<P>
Ellis is still recuperating from injuries he received Jan. 12 when the car he 
was driving was involved in a single-car accident on a northbound on-ramp to 
Interstate 5. He suffered a collapsed lung and three broken ribs. 
</P>
