U.S. NAVY BOXER COLLAPSES, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 23-year-old member of the U.S. Navy boxing team died Thursday at Memorial 
Hospital after collapsing during a Wednesday morning workout. 
</P>
<P>
Petty Officer 3rd Class Tyrone Smith was pronounced dead at 11:06 a.m. after 
surgery to remove a large blood clot, according to El Paso County Deputy 
Coroner Dr. Michael Stewart. 
</P>
<P>
Smith collapsed at 10:30 a.m. Wednesday at the Ft. Carson boxing gymnasium 
where the Navy team was training for next week's USA-Amateur Boxing Federation 
National Championships in Colorado Springs. Medics attempted unsuccessfully to 
revive Smith. He was taken to Memorial Hospital and underwent emergency 
surgery. 
</P>
<P>
The 147-pound boxer was stationed at Norfolk (Va.) Naval Station. He would have 
been making his first appearance in the USA-ABF Championships. 
